sentences: Heiress is an American band from Seattle, Washington, formed in 2006.
They signed to Deathwish Inc. in 2010, and released their debut album Early Frost in 2013.
They signed to Deathwish Inc. in 2010, and released their debut album Early Frost in 2013.
Heiress was founded in Seattle, Washington in 2006 by guitarist Wes Reed.
In December 2008, John Pettibone, formerly of many Seattle-area bands including Himsa and Undertow, took over Paysse's place as lead vocalist.
With this lineup, Heiress recorded a five-song self-titled EP that was self-released by the band in 2009.
In 2010, Heiress signed to Deathwish Inc., an independent hardcore punk record label that was co-founded by Jacob Bannon of Converge.
Endino also remixed two previously recorded Heiress songs.
Deathwish released two of the songs from these sessions, "Naysayer" and "Just Throats," as a 7" vinyl single in 2012.
The single featured artwork by Demian Johnston, who previously played with Pettibone in Undertow and Nineironspitfire, and was positively received by Alternative Press.
In October 2011, Early Frost was expected to be released in 2012.
In October 2011, Early Frost was expected to be released in 2012.
However, Deathwish did not end up releasing the album until 2013 due to pressing plant delays.
Heiress released its second studio album Of Great Sorrow on February 10, 2015 through The Mylene Sheath — pushed back four months from its originally projected November 18, 2014 release date.

Before the release of Of Great Sorrow, Heiress had already begun working on its third studio album with Matt Bayles (Botch, Isis, Mastodon) for a tentative 2015 release.
The band released its third studio album Made Wrong on March 18, 2016 through The Mylene Sheath.
The Band will release their fourth album Distant Fires on October 1, 2021.
